# Diagram Build Specification: Cell-Based Architecture

## Layout

Two-lane horizontal layout per the template specification.

### Control Plane Lane (Top)

Components:
- **Router / Load Balancer**: Receives incoming traffic. Positioned at the left edge of the Control Plane lane.
- **Cell Assignment Service**: Determines which cell handles a given request based on partition key. Positioned center of the Control Plane lane.
- **Health Monitor**: Continuously evaluates cell health. Positioned at the right edge of the Control Plane lane.

Connections:
- Solid black arrow from external traffic (left) into Router.
- Solid gray arrow from Router to Cell Assignment Service.
- Solid gray arrow from Health Monitor to Cell Assignment Service (health status feed).

### Data Plane Lane (Bottom)

Components:
- **Cell A**: Rounded rectangle. Contains: Compute, Queue, Data Store. Label: "Cell A — Partition 1-1000."
- **Cell B**: Rounded rectangle. Contains: Compute, Queue, Data Store. Label: "Cell B — Partition 1001-2000."
- **Cell C**: Rounded rectangle. Contains: Compute, Queue, Data Store. Label: "Cell C — Partition 2001-3000."

Each cell is self-contained. No arrows between cells.

Connections:
- Solid gray arrow from Cell Assignment Service down to each cell (routing).

### Failure Boundary

- Dashed red rectangle around Cell B only.
- Label: "Failure Boundary — Blast radius limited to Partition 1001-2000."
- Dashed red arrow from Cell B's Data Store to the failure boundary label.

### Shared Dependency Box

- Dotted-border rectangle below the cells, labeled "Global Configuration Store."
- Dotted gray lines from each cell to this box.
- Note: This is the single point of shared risk. The article discusses static stability to mitigate this.

## Color Palette

Per template specification:
- Control Plane background: #F5F5F5
- Data Plane background: #FFFFFF
- Cell borders: #333333
- Cell fill: #E8EEF2
- Failure boundary: #CC0000 dashed
- Arrows: #000000 (traffic), #666666 (routing)
- Shared dependency: #999999 dotted

